race.comment: DIDN'T MISS MANY (6) resumed on a heavy track at Pakenham over 1400m and then found more like his best, beaten a whisker at Werribee. He's raced well in stronger than this and is proven third-up. Kersley rides today and he can go one better. HE'S GODSPEED (5) was back to form, winning a 62 at Terang over 1200m. Has an awkward barrier but has won this course and distance and has each way claims. ROSE OF SHALAA (13) comes out of the same race beaten less than 2L. It was a tough effort from the 13 gate, and she's still shy of her best. Keeps Yendall and with average luck can feature. LETHAL THOUGHTS (1) is proving hard to catch but has the ability and has a senior hoop aboard for the first time in a while. In the premier stable and can't be taken lightly.
